We now believe that the issue was that the seeds in question were 
returning redirects to a different URI, which the regex prefetch URI 
filter was disallowing.

There was no indication in any of the logs that this was the reason for 
the -50/deferred.  Instead, we just kept playing around with the job 
until we could get it to crawl properly, and then analyzed the 
problematic part of the job specification.  This does point up the need 
for Heritrix to be capable of much more extensive auditing - so that you 
can see precisely what happened to a seed (or any document URI).

Thanks,
Karl
